  priority: P0
  title: Populate intent registry with current priorities
  description: 'Create the intent_registry.yaml file at /opt/nexus/automation/intent_registry.yaml
    with all P0-P3 tasks defined. This is the gate for Prompt 23''s planning engine.
    The orchestrator reads this file to determine what to execute next. Without it,
    the autonomous system has no instructions.

    '
  acceptance_criteria:
  - intent_registry.yaml exists at /opt/nexus/automation/intent_registry.yaml
  - File parses as valid YAML with no errors
  - 'All intents have required fields: id, category, title, description, acceptance_criteria,
    depends_on, autonomous, risk, complexity'
  - Planning engine from Prompt 23 can read and select the next task from this file
  affected_files:
  - /opt/nexus/automation/intent_registry.yaml
  depends_on: []
  autonomous: false
  risk: low
  complexity: low
  tier1_required: false
  status: completed
- id: ns-002
  category: next_step
  priority: P1
  title: Flash Pi Pico 2s as HID keyboard and mouse
  description: 'Flash both Pi Pico 2s attached to nexus-admin with CircuitPython and
    adafruit_hid. Pico A becomes a programmable USB keyboard, Pico B becomes a programmable
    USB mouse. Write a Python control library at /opt/nexus/automation/hid_controller.py
    on nexus-admin that exposes functions: type_text(), press_key(), key_combo(),
    move_mouse(x, y), click(), right_click(), scroll(). The orchestrator imports this
    library to physically interact with nexus-admin''s desktop or any machine the
    Picos are plugged into.

    '
  acceptance_criteria:
  - Pico A recognized as USB keyboard by nexus-admin (ls /dev/ttyACM* or /dev/hidraw*)
  - Pico B recognized as USB mouse by nexus-admin
  - hid_controller.type_text('hello world') types into whatever window is focused
  - hid_controller.click(x, y) moves cursor to coordinates and clicks
  - Round-trip latency under 200ms per command
  affected_files:
  - /opt/nexus/automation/hid_controller.py
  - /opt/nexus/automation/pico_firmware/keyboard_hid.py
  - /opt/nexus/automation/pico_firmware/mouse_hid.py
  depends_on: []
  autonomous: true
  risk: low
  complexity: low
  tier1_required: false
  status: completed
- id: ns-003
  category: next_step
  priority: P1
  title: Deploy Ollama subagent on spare cluster node
  description: 'Identify which Pi node has the most available headroom (nexus-storage
    at 0.8% CPU and 137MB Geth is the likely candidate). Install Ollama, pull a small
    model (Qwen2.5-1.5B-Instruct or SmolLM2-1.7B, both fit in ~2GB RAM on ARM64).
    Configure to listen on local network at <node-ip>:11434. Write a thin Python client
    at /opt/nexus/automation/subagent_client.py that the orchestrator calls with functions:
    subagent.summarize(text), subagent.review_code(filepath), subagent.research(query).
    Each call gets an ECT cost assigned so the token economy tracks subagent usage.
    Must not degrade Geth or IPFS performance on the host node.

    '
  acceptance_criteria:
  - Ollama running as systemd service on chosen node
  - curl http://<node-ip>:11434/api/generate returns a response
  - subagent_client.py successfully delegates a summarize task and returns result
  - Response latency under 30 seconds for a 500-token prompt
  - Geth and IPFS on same node remain unaffected (CPU stays under 50% during inference)
  affected_files:
  - /opt/nexus/automation/subagent_client.py
  - /opt/nexus/automation/constitution.json
  - /etc/systemd/system/ollama.service
  depends_on: []
  autonomous: false
  risk: medium
  complexity: medium
  tier1_required: false
  status: completed
