- id: rm-001
  category: roadmap
  priority: P3
  title: Action-to-transaction encoding protocol
  description: "Design and implement the encoding standard that converts any system\
    \ action into a structured blockchain transaction the internal system can decode.\
    \ When User 1 does Action X at Time Y, the system encodes: from address (actor\
    \ wallet or agent wallet), to address (target contract \u2014 ActionRegistry),\
    \ data field (ABI-encoded payload with action type, parameters, timestamp), and\
    \ the tx hash becomes the permanent unique receipt. Define 5-10 initial action\
    \ types: user_login, file_access, agent_decision, resource_allocation, config_change.\
    \ Build complete encode/decode cycle. This is the foundational protocol that makes\
    \ blockchain-as-kernel real rather than metaphorical.\n"
  acceptance_criteria:
  - Encoding protocol spec documented with field definitions and ABI format
  - 'Python encoder: action_to_tx(actor, action_type, params) returns signed transaction'
  - 'Python decoder: tx_to_action(tx_hash) returns actor, action_type, params, timestamp'
  - 'Round-trip demo: action > encode > submit > confirm > decode > matches original'
  - 5-10 action types defined with unique type IDs
  affected_files:
  - /opt/nexus/contracts/source/ActionRegistry.sol
  - /opt/nexus/automation/action_encoder.py
  - /opt/nexus/automation/action_decoder.py
  - /opt/nexus/docs/encoding_protocol.md
  depends_on: []
  autonomous: true
  risk: medium
  complexity: medium
  tier1_required: false
  status: decomposed
- id: rm-002
  category: roadmap
  priority: P3
  title: ActionRegistry smart contract
  description: 'Deploy a general-purpose ActionRegistry smart contract on Chain ID
    123454321. Accepts encoded action transactions, indexes by actor address and action
    type, emits events for off-chain indexers. Provides view functions: getActionsByActor(address,
    fromBlock, toBlock) and getActionsByType(uint8, fromBlock, toBlock). Gas-efficient:
    relies on event logs for historical queries, stores only latest state per actor.
    Integrates with existing ECT/RST token contracts. This is the system call table
    of NEXUS OS.

    '
  acceptance_criteria:
  - Contract deployed on Chain ID 123454321
  - Processes 100+ test actions across multiple types and actors
  - Python indexer reconstructs full action history from chain in under 10 seconds
  - Event emissions for all action types verified
  - Gas cost per action under 100k gas
  affected_files:
  - /opt/nexus/contracts/source/ActionRegistry.sol
  - /opt/nexus/contracts/deployed/ActionRegistry.json
  - /opt/nexus/contracts/scripts/deploy_action_registry.py
  - /opt/nexus/contracts/scripts/test_action_registry.py
  depends_on:
