  autonomous: true
  risk: medium
  complexity: medium
  tier1_required: false
  status: decomposed
- id: rm-003
  category: roadmap
  priority: P3
  title: Transaction decoder and internal lookup algorithm
  description: 'Always-running service on the cluster that watches the blockchain
    and maintains a decoded index of all transactions. On each new block: read every
    transaction, identify target contract, decode ABI data, write record to local
    SQLite index. Lookup API answers: What did wallet 0xABC do last hour? Show all
    file_access actions today. Full CEO agent decision history. Which action produced
    tx 0x123? Starts with polling (every 5s matching block period), optimizes to event
    subscriptions later. Feeds into Command Center dashboard for live chain view.

    '
  acceptance_criteria:
  - Decoder service runs continuously as systemd service
  - Processes new blocks in real-time (within 5s of block creation)
  - Lookup API responds to queries with decoded results within 1 second
  - SQLite index stores decoded actions with full metadata
  - Command Center dashboard shows live chain activity in plain language
  affected_files:
  - /opt/nexus/automation/tx_decoder_service.py
  - /opt/nexus/automation/tx_index.db
  - /opt/nexus/dashboard/
  - /etc/systemd/system/nexus-decoder.service
  depends_on:
