  autonomous: true
  risk: low
  complexity: high
  tier1_required: false
  status: decomposed
- id: rm-004
  category: roadmap
  priority: P3
  title: ECT/RST token integration with action costs
  description: 'Map each action type to its ECT cost and RST stake requirement. Extend
    beyond agent decisions to all system actions. File access: 1 ECT. Config change:
    10 ECT + 100 RST staked. Contract deploy: 50 ECT + 500 RST staked. ActionRegistry
    checks balances before accepting transactions, reverts if actor cannot afford
    it. Creates natural rate limiting, accountability, and economic signal. Token
    economy dashboard in Command Center shows spend rates per agent and per action
    type.

    '
  acceptance_criteria:
  - At least 5 action types have defined ECT costs and RST requirements
  - Insufficient ECT balance causes transaction revert with clear error
  - Token economy view in Command Center shows spend rates per agent and action type
  - RST staking enforced for high-risk actions
  - Daily ECT budget replenishment logic implemented
  affected_files:
